library(microbenchmark)

fun1 <- function(mat) {
  n <- nrow(mat)
  ans <- double(n) 
  for (i in 1:n) {
    ans[i] <- sum(mat[i, ])
  }
  ans
}


fun2 <- function(mat) {
  n <- nrow(mat)
  k <- ncol(mat)
  ans <- mat
  for (i in 1:n) {
    for (j in 2:k) {
      ans[i,j] <- mat[i, j] + ans[i, j - 1]
    }
  }
  ans
}

fun1alt <- function(mat) {
  rowSums(mat)
}

fun2alt <- function(mat) {
  t(apply(mat, 1, cumsum))
}


set.seed(2315)
dat <- matrix(rnorm(200 * 100), nrow = 200)
identical(fun1(dat), fun1alt(dat))
[1] TRUE
all.equal(fun1(dat), fun1alt(dat))
[1] TRUE
identical(fun2(dat), fun2alt(dat))
[1] TRUE
all.equal(fun2(dat), fun2alt(dat))
[1] TRUE

  fun1(dat),
  fun1alt(dat),
  unit = "relative"
)

fun1 <- function(mat) {
  n <- nrow(mat)
  ans <- double(n)
  for (i in 1:n) {
    ans[i] <- sum(mat[i, ])
  }
  ans
}

fun1alt <- function(mat) {
  rowSums(mat)
}

fun2 <- function(mat) {
  n <- nrow(mat)
  k <- ncol(mat)
  ans <- mat
  for (i in 1:n) {
    for (j in 2:k) {
      ans[i,j] <- mat[i, j] + ans[i, j - 1]
    }
  }
  ans
}

fun2alt <- function(mat) {
  t(apply(mat, 1, cumsum))
}

  fun1 = fun1(dat),
  fun1alt = fun1alt(dat),
  fun2 = fun2(dat),
  fun2alt = fun2alt(dat),
  times = 50
)


bench_df <- as.data.frame(bench) %>%
  group_by(expr) %>%
  summarize(median_time = median(time) / 1e6)   # convert ns â ms

  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +

    plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"),

fun1 <- function(mat) {
  n <- nrow(mat)
  ans <- double(n) 
  for (i in 1:n) {
    ans[i] <- sum(mat[i, ])
  }
  ans
}

fun2 <- function(mat) {
  n <- nrow(mat)
  k <- ncol(mat)
  ans <- mat
  for (i in 1:n) {
    for (j in 2:k) {
      ans[i,j] <- mat[i, j] + ans[i, j - 1]
    }
  }
  ans
}


fun1alt <- function(mat) rowSums(mat)
fun2alt <- function(mat) t(apply(mat, 1, cumsum))


set.seed(2315)
dat <- matrix(rnorm(200 * 100), nrow = 200)

bench <- microbenchmark(
  fun1 = fun1(dat),
  fun1alt = fun1alt(dat),
  fun2 = fun2(dat),
  fun2alt = fun2alt(dat),
  times = 50
)

bench_df <- as.data.frame(bench) %>%
  group_by(expr) %>%
  summarise(median_ms = median(time) / 1e6)

ggplot(bench_df, aes(x = expr, y = median_ms, fill = expr)) +
  geom_col(color = "black") +

    values = c(

library(parallel)

sim_pi <- function(n = 1000, i = NULL) {
  p <- matrix(runif(n*2), ncol = 2)
  mean(rowSums(p^2) < 1) * 4
}
system.time({
  

  cl <- makeCluster(detectCores() - 1)

  clusterExport(cl, c("sim_pi"))
  
  ans <- parLapply(cl, 1:4000, function(i) sim_pi(n = 10000))
  ans <- unlist(ans)

  print(mean(ans))
  
  stopCluster(cl)
})

sim_pi <- function(n = 1000, i = NULL) {
  p <- matrix(runif(n*2), ncol = 2)
  mean(rowSums(p^2) < 1) * 4
}

set.seed(1231)
serial_time <- system.time({
  ans_serial <- unlist(lapply(1:4000, sim_pi, n = 10000))
})

library(parallel)

set.seed(1231)
parallel_time <- system.time({
  cl <- makeCluster(detectCores() - 1)
  clusterExport(cl, "sim_pi")

  ans_parallel <- parLapply(cl, 1:4000, function(i) sim_pi(10000))
  ans_parallel <- unlist(ans_parallel)

  stopCluster(cl)
})

   user  system elapsed 
  0.006   0.005   0.644

library(RSQLite)
library(DBI)

con <- dbConnect(SQLite(), ":memory:")

film <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ivanceras/sakila/master/csv-sakila-db/film.csv")
film_category <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ivanceras/sakila/master/csv-sakila-db/film_category.csv")
category <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ivanceras/sakila/master/csv-sakila-db/category.csv")

dbWriteTable(con, "film", film)
dbWriteTable(con, "film_category", film_category)
dbWriteTable(con, "category", category)

library(tidyr)

rating_avgs <- dbGetQuery(con, "
  SELECT 
      rating,
      AVG(replacement_cost) AS avg_replacement_cost,
      AVG(rental_rate) AS avg_rental_rate
  FROM film
  GROUP BY rating
  ORDER BY rating;
")

df_long <- pivot_longer(
  rating_avgs,
  cols = c(avg_replacement_cost, avg_rental_rate),
  names_to = "metric",
  values_to = "value"
)

ggplot(df_long, aes(x = rating, y = value, fill = metric)) +
  geom_col(position = position_dodge(width = 0.8), color = "black") +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Blues", direction = 1,
                    labels = c("Avg Replacement Cost", "Avg Rental Rate")) +
  labs(
    title = "Average Replacement Cost and Rental Rate by Rating Category",
    x = "Rating Category",
    y = "Value (USD)",
    fill = "Metric"
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
    legend.position = "top"
  )

SELECT 
    c.name AS category_name,
    COUNT(*) AS film_count
FROM film_category AS fc
INNER JOIN film AS f
    ON fc.film_id = f.film_id
INNER JOIN category AS c
    ON fc.category_id = c.category_id
GROUP BY c.category_id, c.name
ORDER BY film_count DESC
LIMIT 1;
1 records
category_name film_count
Sports 74

The most popular category is: Sports (with 74 films)

film_counts <- dbGetQuery(con, "
  SELECT 
      c.name AS category_name,
      COUNT(*) AS film_count
  FROM film_category AS fc
  INNER JOIN film AS f
      ON fc.film_id = f.film_id
  INNER JOIN category AS c
      ON fc.category_id = c.category_id
  GROUP BY c.category_id, c.name
  ORDER BY film_count DESC;
")
top_category <- film_counts$category_name[1]

film_counts <- film_counts %>%
  mutate(
    highlight = ifelse(category_name == top_category, "Most Popular", "Other")
  )

ggplot(film_counts, aes(
  x = reorder(category_name, film_count),
  y = film_count,
  fill = highlight
)) +
  geom_col(color = "black") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(
    "Most Popular" = "#08306B",  
    "Other" = "#6BAED6"          
  )) +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(
    title = paste("Most Popular Category:", top_category),
    x = "Category",
    y = "Number of Films",
    fill = ""
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +
  theme(
    legend.position = "top",
    plot.title = element_text(face = "bold")
  )
